    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "with readline interaction and potentially different implementations on different platforms this seems pretty difficult to fix.  out of curiosity, I tried these things in separate tests just before pressing control-d to exit.. in every case the up arrow behaviour was the same:\n\n> > get_ipython().readline.set_completer(None)\n> > get_ipython().history_manager.input_hist_parsed = sh.history_manager.input_hist_raw=[]\n> > get_ipython().readline.clear_history()\n\nnot a big surprise since (for me at least) the default exit behaviour completion for ipython is exactly the same as vanilla python using raw_input().\n"
  },
